<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>⚡ Daily Planner — Make the Counter Buttons</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Wire three buttons to change a number and show it on the page — <code>getElementById</code>, <code>addEventListener</code>, <code>count</code>, <code>textContent</code> · <strong>Course:</strong> Web Dev: JavaScript · <strong>Time:</strong> about 50 minutes</p>
<p>You built a Daily Planner page with three buttons: <strong>increase</strong>, <strong>decrease</strong>, and <strong>square</strong>. Now you make them work. Each button changes a <strong>count</strong>, and a text field shows the new number. First you read code and predict, then you fix broken code, then you wire all three buttons yourself.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧠 Words to know: <strong>getElementById</strong>, <strong>addEventListener</strong>, <strong>count</strong>, <strong>textContent</strong>, <strong>square</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each piece of code. Work out what happens, then write your prediction.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">let count = 0;
count = count + 1;
count = count + 1;
console.log(count);
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What number prints?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-javascript">let count = 3;
count = count * count;
console.log(count);
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What does <code>count</code> become? What does "square" mean here?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;p id=&quot;clicksCounter&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
  const clicksCounter = document.getElementById(&quot;clicksCounter&quot;);
  clicksCounter.textContent = &quot;Clicks: 5&quot;;
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> started empty. What text shows on the page now?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-javascript">btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
  count = count + 1;
  clicksCounter.textContent = &quot;Clicks: &quot; + count;
});
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The page shows <code>Clicks: 0</code>. You click the button three times. What does it show?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each block is broken. Read what it is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, write the fix, then explain why the original was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This should grab the increase button, whose id in the HTML is <code>btnInc</code>. Right now <code>btn</code> ends up empty, so nothing works.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">const btn = document.getElementById(&quot;btn&quot;);
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the id inside <code>getElementById(" ")</code> must match the id in the HTML exactly.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — Clicking Increase should add <strong>1</strong>. Right now it adds <strong>3</strong> every click.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
  count = count + 1;
});
btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
  count = count + 1;
});
btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
  count = count + 1;
});
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> how many times did you tell the button to listen? Every listener runs on every click.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The Decrease button should take <strong>1</strong> away from count. Right now clicking it does nothing.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">const btnDec = document.getElementById(&quot;btnDec&quot;);

// the increase button is wired, but nothing here talks to btnDec
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a button only reacts if you add an <code>addEventListener</code> to it.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>Read this working <strong>increase</strong> button carefully. It is the pattern you will copy for the other two.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;button id=&quot;btnInc&quot;&gt;increase&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;clicksCounter&quot;&gt;Count: 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
  const btnInc = document.getElementById(&quot;btnInc&quot;);
  const clicksCounter = document.getElementById(&quot;clicksCounter&quot;);
  let count = 0;

  btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
    count = count + 1;
    clicksCounter.textContent = &quot;Count: &quot; + count;
  });
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which line makes the starting count, and what number does it start at?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What does <code>document.getElementById("btnInc")</code> give you?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Inside the click function, two things happen every click. Name both, in order.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What does <code>textContent</code> change — the code, or the words shown on the page?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Your Assignment: Three Buttons 🔨</h2>
<p>Now make all three buttons work on your Daily Planner. Open your <code>scripts.js</code>.</p>
<p>Your page already has these:</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;button id=&quot;btnInc&quot;&gt;increase&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button id=&quot;btnDec&quot;&gt;decrease&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button id=&quot;btnSqu&quot;&gt;square&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;clicksCounter&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>Make each button change <code>count</code>, then show the new number in <code>clicksCounter</code>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Increase</strong> — <code>btnInc</code> adds 1 to count.</li>
<li><strong>Decrease</strong> — <code>btnDec</code> takes 1 away from count.</li>
<li><strong>Square</strong> — <code>btnSqu</code> multiplies count by itself: <code>count = count * count</code>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Start from this. Finish the two <code>TODO</code> buttons the same way as increase:</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">const btnInc = document.getElementById(&quot;btnInc&quot;);
const btnDec = document.getElementById(&quot;btnDec&quot;);
const btnSqu = document.getElementById(&quot;btnSqu&quot;);
const clicksCounter = document.getElementById(&quot;clicksCounter&quot;);
let count = 0;

btnInc.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function () {
  count = count + 1;
  clicksCounter.textContent = &quot;Count: &quot; + count;
});

// TODO: btnDec — take 1 away from count, then show it
// TODO: btnSqu — multiply count by itself, then show it
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the two listeners you added (decrease and square):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Test it: set count to 3, then click square. What number shows? Click square again — what shows now?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on a phone while your page runs. Talk like you are teaching someone new. Try to use these words: <strong>button</strong>, <strong>addEventListener</strong>, <strong>count</strong>, <strong>textContent</strong>, <strong>square</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your page, then click each button and watch the number change.</li>
<li>Read your <strong>square</strong> button's code out loud and say what it does.</li>
<li>Point to the line that shows the number on the page.</li>
<li>Say what happens to the count when you click square twice.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video. Plan it here before you record.</strong></p>
